WEBVTT

00:01.535 --> 00:03.301
<i> Bon-jour tout le mond-e!</i>

00:03.303 --> 00:04.636
Adult mark:<i> French class.</i>

00:04.672 --> 00:06.038
<i> Bonjour, ma soeur rose.</i>

00:06.040 --> 00:07.172
Adult mark:<i> I hated it.</i>

00:07.174 --> 00:08.507
<i> Comment allez-vous?</i>

00:08.642 --> 00:09.908
[class muttering replies]

00:09.910 --> 00:11.009
Adult mark:<i> The</i>
<i> newfoundland accent</i>

00:11.045 --> 00:12.944
<i>Was not meant to parlez-vous.</i>

00:12.980 --> 00:18.250
Can anyone in this class form
even one sentence in french?

00:18.252 --> 00:19.585
Mr. Critch?

00:19.720 --> 00:21.386
Adult mark:<i> The only</i>
<i> french words I knew</i>

00:21.389 --> 00:23.489
<i> Were the ones that meant</i>
<i> the same in english.</i>

00:23.624 --> 00:25.990
<i> Je suis...</i>

00:26.027 --> 00:28.793
<i> Allé à la matinée...</i>

00:30.664 --> 00:34.899
<i> Avec... Ma fiancée...</i>

00:34.935 --> 00:36.802
<i> Encore!</i>

00:36.871 --> 00:38.570
Adult mark:<i> I barely</i>
<i> knew any french</i>

00:38.606 --> 00:40.472
<i> But that was still more</i>
<i> than my french teacher knew.</i>

00:40.541 --> 00:41.739
<i> Bien.</i>

00:41.776 --> 00:43.942
<i> Bi-en!</i>

00:44.011 --> 00:45.611
Sister rose: Anyone else?

00:45.746 --> 00:48.747
[laughs]
you're a brain, idiot.

00:48.882 --> 00:50.715
Adult mark:<i> There was nothing</i>
<i> more shameful at school</i>

00:50.785 --> 00:52.417
<i> Than being smart.</i>

00:52.420 --> 00:56.087
You'll all have to do much
better before our european trip!

00:56.123 --> 00:57.756
Adult mark:<i> Each year,</i>
<i> the grade eights travelled</i>

00:57.891 --> 00:59.258
<i>To europe for french immersion!</i>

00:59.393 --> 01:01.025
<i> Who didn't love France?</i>

01:01.162 --> 01:03.428
France is a horrible place,
children.

01:03.431 --> 01:06.298
Bicycles.
Nude statues.

01:06.367 --> 01:09.367
The foul stench
of wine and cheese

01:09.403 --> 01:12.704
Intermingling on the lips...

01:12.773 --> 01:14.573
As they...

01:14.642 --> 01:18.110
French kiss.

01:18.245 --> 01:22.647
That is why I expect you to
behave the way jesus would have.

01:22.716 --> 01:24.783
Like north americans!

01:24.918 --> 01:27.519
Adult mark:<i> I knew that</i>
<i> the french would get moi.</i>

01:27.654 --> 01:30.188
<i> Romance, art,</i>
<i> jerry lewis movies?</i>

01:30.324 --> 01:32.257
<i> I could reinvent myself there!</i>

01:32.293 --> 01:35.793
<i> And maybe impress fox</i>
<i> with my "je ne sais quoi."</i>

01:35.830 --> 01:39.731
[accordion music]

01:39.733 --> 01:42.067
<i> Excusez-moi, madame?</i>

01:42.069 --> 01:43.769
<i> Est-ce que je vous connais?</i>

01:43.771 --> 01:45.170
<i> Croyez-vous en l'amour?</i>

01:45.305 --> 01:47.506
<i> L'amour?</i>

01:47.641 --> 01:51.543
<i> ♪</i>

01:51.579 --> 01:56.582
<i> L'amour est aussi</i>
<i> proche que mes lèvres.</i>

01:56.584 --> 01:59.250
Hey, dumbass!

02:03.323 --> 02:04.490
Why is it so close?

02:04.625 --> 02:06.224
What?

02:06.360 --> 02:07.226
That can't be right.

02:07.361 --> 02:09.427
Luckily,
we don't have to go to France,

02:09.463 --> 02:12.164
For France has come to us.

02:12.166 --> 02:13.499
Adult mark:<i> St. Pierre</i>
<i> and miquelon</i>

02:13.634 --> 02:14.933
<i> Is a tiny french island</i>

02:15.068 --> 02:17.836
<i> Just 19 kilometres</i>
<i> off the coast of newfoundland.</i>

02:17.838 --> 02:19.238
What a rip!
That's not France.

02:19.373 --> 02:21.340
<i> En français!</i>

02:21.342 --> 02:23.241
<i> Zut alors!</i>
Ca c'est de la merde!

02:23.310 --> 02:25.177
Adult mark:<i> Fox was</i>
<i> fluent in swearing,</i>

02:25.179 --> 02:26.978
<i> But sister rose</i>
<i> hadn't heard those words</i>

02:27.047 --> 02:28.246
<i> In either language.</i>

02:28.282 --> 02:29.981
Excellent, fox.

02:30.017 --> 02:33.652
When England won
the seven years' war in 1763,

02:33.721 --> 02:35.320
They got newfoundland,

02:35.356 --> 02:39.057
And France got these
two tiny islands.

02:39.126 --> 02:42.460
So we are going to France.

02:42.462 --> 02:43.661
Technically.

02:43.697 --> 02:46.398
Adult mark:<i> No eiffel tower,</i>
<i> no louvre.</i>

02:46.533 --> 02:48.266
<i> My dreams were "fini."</i>

02:48.335 --> 02:50.068
It's three
friggin' hours on a bus!

02:50.204 --> 02:51.603
You better sit with me.

02:51.738 --> 02:53.672
Adult mark:<i> Well,</i>
<i> then again...</i>

02:53.674 --> 02:55.507
I don't want to be
stuck with some loser.

02:55.509 --> 02:56.641
Adult mark:<i> Impossible!</i>

02:56.677 --> 02:59.411
<i> N'est pas français.</i>

02:59.413 --> 03:02.013
♪

03:02.148 --> 03:03.448
Please, can I go?

03:03.517 --> 03:05.250
I don't know, mark,
it's awful far.

03:05.385 --> 03:07.219
Almost four-hour drive
with the ferry.

03:07.354 --> 03:08.754
Pop: Well...

03:08.889 --> 03:10.956
I suppose I could
chaperone, you know?

03:11.091 --> 03:13.091
I haven't been abroad before.

03:13.093 --> 03:15.060
You had your chance
with two world wars.

03:15.195 --> 03:16.828
Weren't too concerned about
seeing France back then,

03:16.964 --> 03:17.729
Were ya?

03:17.731 --> 03:20.198
Colour-blind.

03:20.234 --> 03:22.367
I think it could be lovely
for him to see the world

03:22.369 --> 03:23.635
Before he dies.

03:23.671 --> 03:26.337
Whoa, who said anything
about dying here?!

03:26.373 --> 03:27.839
I-I guess I could ask?

03:27.841 --> 03:29.374
Hey, excellent.
Heh!

03:29.410 --> 03:31.175
Now, just leave a little room

03:31.212 --> 03:33.512
In your suitcase for duty-free.

03:33.647 --> 03:36.314
Hm?
Hm.

03:36.450 --> 03:38.283
So...?

03:38.352 --> 03:39.517
Alright.

03:39.553 --> 03:40.985
[exhales]
yes!

03:43.590 --> 03:45.090
-Mike?
-Mm-hm?

03:45.225 --> 03:46.324
I had a thought.

03:46.360 --> 03:47.925
Mm-hm?

03:47.962 --> 03:49.994
With mark and pop
gone to europe...

03:50.030 --> 03:51.195
Oh, yeah.

03:51.232 --> 03:52.530
And mike jr. At work...

03:52.600 --> 03:53.799
Yes, yeah...

03:53.934 --> 03:55.934
We're gonna have
the house all to ourselves...

03:55.936 --> 03:57.368
Mm-hm.

03:57.404 --> 03:59.537
Mary: All alone...

03:59.607 --> 04:02.874
For the first time
in seventeen years.

04:05.746 --> 04:09.214
We could get to bed
a little bit early.

04:09.349 --> 04:11.716
I could use the sleep!

04:17.023 --> 04:18.890
Windows stay closed.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.493
No unscheduled bathroom breaks.

04:21.628 --> 04:26.498
Like moses and the red sea,
this aisle will remain parted.

04:26.500 --> 04:28.232
Those are the rules!

04:28.269 --> 04:30.568
Excuse me, sister...

04:30.570 --> 04:34.272
Do you mind if I just
squeeze past your arse?

04:36.310 --> 04:38.976
Boys and girls!

04:39.013 --> 04:43.648
[rock music]

04:43.684 --> 04:45.984
Bonjour, mes amis!

04:46.119 --> 04:47.719
Woo!
Next stop europe!

04:47.854 --> 04:49.120
Excited?

04:49.156 --> 04:51.189
It's not real France.
It's just a knock-off.

04:51.191 --> 04:52.724
Oh, come on!

04:52.859 --> 04:56.495
Where's your sense of adventure,
little miss red, huh?

04:56.497 --> 04:59.197
Do you know what
st. Pierre is famous for?

04:59.199 --> 05:00.632
Sucking?

05:00.634 --> 05:01.867
No.

05:01.869 --> 05:03.201
Rum running!

05:03.336 --> 05:04.836
Prohibition!

05:04.872 --> 05:09.341
See, booze used to be illegal
then, like drugs are today.

05:09.343 --> 05:12.544
Oh no, st. Pierre was
a bootlegger's dream!

05:12.546 --> 05:14.980
Now, quiz!

05:14.982 --> 05:17.683
Who knows who al capone is?

05:17.818 --> 05:18.950
The gangster?

05:18.952 --> 05:20.118
Yeah!

05:20.254 --> 05:22.220
He's robert deniro!
From the untouchables!

05:22.289 --> 05:23.955
-Oh, yeah!
-Will you two shut it?

05:23.991 --> 05:25.791
Go ahead, old man.

05:25.793 --> 05:27.525
I mean, mr. Critch.

05:27.527 --> 05:30.829
Hm, well,
he needed illegal booze

05:30.898 --> 05:32.097
For his night clubs,

05:32.232 --> 05:35.300
So he had 80 boats sneaking

05:35.435 --> 05:39.637
300,000 cases a month from
st. Pierre to newfoundland,

05:39.673 --> 05:42.707
And then they'd smuggle them
across the border to the states.

05:42.710 --> 05:45.410
He got so rich he built a church

05:45.545 --> 05:48.113
Just so that everyone
would look the other way.

05:48.182 --> 05:49.714
Okay.
That's pretty bad-ass!

05:49.750 --> 05:50.849
Oh, yeah.

05:50.851 --> 05:52.183
Can we go see the church?

05:52.219 --> 05:54.419
Sure, sister rose
would love that!

05:54.421 --> 05:56.454
Adult mark:<i> I was beginning</i>
<i> to doubt pop's reasons</i>

05:56.490 --> 05:57.589
<i> For coming.</i>

05:57.658 --> 05:59.224
How do you know
so much about it?

05:59.359 --> 06:02.694
I won't have you filling their
heads with legends and lies.

06:02.696 --> 06:05.396
And I don't know what possessed
you to sign on as a chaperone,

06:05.432 --> 06:07.865
But I know that you could
only be possessed by the devil.

06:07.901 --> 06:10.268
Just clear the aisle, sister.

06:10.337 --> 06:12.203
Those are the rules.

06:12.239 --> 06:15.941
Adult mark:<i> This was</i>
<i> going to be a long trip.</i>

06:16.076 --> 06:19.678
[accordion music]

06:19.680 --> 06:22.748
♪

06:22.883 --> 06:26.284
♪

06:26.420 --> 06:28.754
♪

06:28.889 --> 06:29.888
Adult mark:<i> France!</i>

06:29.957 --> 06:32.090
<i> Words escaped me.</i>

06:32.092 --> 06:34.960
<i> Mostly because</i>
<i> I wasn't good at french.</i>

06:34.962 --> 06:36.828
Did we drive in a circle?

06:36.864 --> 06:38.563
This place looks just like home.

06:38.632 --> 06:40.365
This sucks.

06:40.367 --> 06:42.968
Adult mark:<i> I thought fox</i>
<i>would fall in love with France,</i>

06:43.103 --> 06:45.904
<i> And me, but I guess some</i>
<i> things just don't translate.</i>

06:45.906 --> 06:47.038
[sister rose claps]

06:47.174 --> 06:50.208
<i> Écou-tez, l'enfants!</i>

06:50.244 --> 06:53.645
<i> Main-tenant,</i>
<i> le français sale-ment!</i>

06:53.714 --> 06:56.548
Adult mark:<i> French immersion</i>
<i> became submersion</i>

06:56.683 --> 06:58.583
<i> As sister rose drowned</i>
<i> in the foreign tongue.</i>

06:58.585 --> 07:00.585
<i> L'enfants!</i>
<i> Le museum!</i>

07:00.587 --> 07:03.321
<i> Allez-vous, toute-lemonds!</i>

07:03.390 --> 07:05.523
Oh my lord.

07:05.592 --> 07:09.794
I never realized
you had such a potty mouth.

07:09.797 --> 07:13.532
[rock music sting]

07:19.973 --> 07:22.340
<i> Madame?</i>

07:22.342 --> 07:25.343
<i> Avec moi?</i>

07:25.345 --> 07:27.545
The only thing that sucks
more than your french

07:27.681 --> 07:28.546
Is this trip.

07:28.582 --> 07:31.382
[seagull cawing]

07:31.452 --> 07:32.584
Exotic.

07:32.653 --> 07:33.818
Oh, no.

07:33.821 --> 07:34.752
No--

07:38.859 --> 07:40.025
Mary?

07:40.160 --> 07:41.893
Who broke the table?

07:41.929 --> 07:44.696
It's just the two of us tonight,
so I took the leaf out.

07:44.698 --> 07:46.764
Hm?

07:46.834 --> 07:50.835
[romantic music
with spanish guitar]

07:50.838 --> 07:52.103
What's this?

07:52.172 --> 07:53.338
French onion soup.

07:53.473 --> 07:55.373
Alice lent me the bowls.

07:55.375 --> 07:56.975
I figured everybody else
was in France,

07:57.044 --> 07:58.743
So we should be too.

07:58.879 --> 08:00.979
Onion soup?
I-I don't like onions.

08:01.048 --> 08:03.314
There aren't any onions in it,
silly!

08:03.383 --> 08:06.384
It's just hot water
and french onion soup mix!

08:06.453 --> 08:08.252
What's all this, then?

08:08.288 --> 08:10.922
Swiss cheese.

08:10.958 --> 08:12.724
Swiss, french!

08:12.726 --> 08:15.260
I need a passport
just to eat my supper!

08:15.329 --> 08:16.862
Is there any turkey left?

08:16.997 --> 08:18.930
You couldn't get laid out of
a chicken's arse, ya know that?

08:19.065 --> 08:20.398
Good god!

08:20.534 --> 08:22.334
I'm trying to be romantic,
ya arsehole!

08:22.336 --> 08:23.802
When do we ever really talk?

08:23.937 --> 08:25.270
All you ever do is talk!

08:25.339 --> 08:27.038
Oh, and you never listen!

08:27.040 --> 08:27.806
[phone rings]

08:27.941 --> 08:29.541
I'll get it!

08:32.179 --> 08:34.211
You couldn't get laid
in a cage full'a monkeys

08:34.248 --> 08:36.314
With a fist full'a bananas!

08:40.521 --> 08:41.753
Hello?

08:41.755 --> 08:43.555
Operator: You have
a collect call from...

08:43.557 --> 08:45.523
[rapidly] hey dad, it's me mark
and everything's okay

08:45.658 --> 08:48.293
But a bird pooped on me
but that's good luck, bye!

08:48.362 --> 08:49.627
Adult mark:<i> Why pay</i>
<i> long distance</i>

08:49.696 --> 08:51.562
<i> When you could jam</i>
<i> all you had to say</i>

08:51.598 --> 08:53.197
<i> Into the space</i>
<i> for the caller's name?</i>

08:53.267 --> 08:54.666
Operator: Will you
accept the charges?

08:54.801 --> 08:56.167
God, no.

08:56.303 --> 08:59.503
Adult mark:<i> It was like</i>
<i> an audio postcard.</i>

08:59.540 --> 09:01.873
Oh, that was mark.
He's fine.

09:01.875 --> 09:04.308
Good.

09:04.344 --> 09:05.944
No more interruptions.

09:05.946 --> 09:07.912
You're gonna have
a romantic night tonight

09:07.948 --> 09:10.214
If it friggin' kills ya!

09:10.284 --> 09:12.350
[dial tone]

09:12.485 --> 09:13.451
Phone's off the hook.

09:13.520 --> 09:14.786
I know.

09:14.855 --> 09:16.521
You know, dad...

09:16.523 --> 09:17.989
A woman needs to be romanced.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.857
Will you get out of it!

09:26.366 --> 09:28.333
<i> Les îles saint-pierre et</i>
<i> miquelon étaient une plaque</i>

09:28.402 --> 09:33.071
<i>Tournante pour la contrebande</i>
<i>d'alcool vers les états-unis.</i>

09:33.073 --> 09:34.405
-What's she saying?
-Shh!

09:34.441 --> 09:37.342
<i> Des criminels notoires</i>
<i> s'y sont installés,</i>

09:37.411 --> 09:41.145
<i> Notamment al capone.</i>

09:41.214 --> 09:42.814
She just said "al capone"!

09:42.883 --> 09:44.349
Your pop was right!

09:44.484 --> 09:46.017
Ah, yes!
Good ear.

09:46.152 --> 09:47.485
<i> Joyeux noël!</i>

09:47.621 --> 09:49.020
<i> Y a-t-il des questions?</i>

09:49.155 --> 09:50.321
<i> Madame?</i>

09:50.390 --> 09:51.489
<i> Oui, madame?</i>

09:51.625 --> 09:54.225
<i> Qu'est-ce que c'est?</i>

09:54.361 --> 09:57.695
<i> Une guillotine.</i>

09:57.831 --> 09:58.730
<i> Ça gère!</i>

09:58.865 --> 09:59.930
<i> Oui, tres bien!</i>

09:59.967 --> 10:00.899
Brain!

10:01.034 --> 10:01.899
What a loser!

10:01.969 --> 10:03.434
Silence!

10:03.470 --> 10:06.905
As you can see, my students
speak french fluently.

10:07.040 --> 10:10.975
If you like, you could practice
your english for a bit?

10:10.978 --> 10:13.077
[heavily accented]
uh... My english?

10:13.113 --> 10:16.213
Uh, yes,
I speak english very well.

10:24.124 --> 10:28.994
[mysterious music]

10:29.129 --> 10:31.996
Al capone's hat.

10:32.032 --> 10:34.999
Huh.

10:35.035 --> 10:37.869
Is that so?

10:38.004 --> 10:41.606
[mysterious music continues]

10:41.675 --> 10:45.276
♪

10:45.345 --> 10:48.880
♪

10:48.949 --> 10:52.283
If the nun can frig off,
so can we.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.152
<i> Excusez-moi?</i>

10:54.154 --> 10:55.653
<i> Vous allez ou?</i>

10:55.656 --> 10:59.457
Sorry.
No speak-ez le french-ez.

11:07.701 --> 11:09.633
Adult mark:<i> Pop</i>
<i> was up to no good,</i>

11:09.670 --> 11:13.104
<i> But this was my chance to show</i>
<i> fox my sophisticated side.</i>

11:13.239 --> 11:16.974
♪

11:17.044 --> 11:20.045
♪

11:20.180 --> 11:23.781
♪

11:26.853 --> 11:29.320
[in a whisper]
patrick?

11:32.392 --> 11:34.525
Patrick?

11:36.596 --> 11:37.595
Rosy!

11:37.664 --> 11:38.730
Aah!
Jesus!

11:38.865 --> 11:41.499
Shh, they'll hear you,
for goodness sake.

11:41.634 --> 11:43.868
Besides, we're in
a house of worship.

11:43.937 --> 11:46.271
It's a little late for
you to find god, isn't it?

11:46.406 --> 11:48.639
Somebody must be
looking down on me.

11:48.709 --> 11:50.408
They brought me to you,
didn't they?

11:50.410 --> 11:52.409
Oh, don't start!

11:52.446 --> 11:54.545
Tell me the real
reason you're here.

11:57.718 --> 11:59.884
[sighs]

11:59.920 --> 12:05.423
[mysterious music]

12:05.425 --> 12:07.091
Fine.

12:07.094 --> 12:09.193
[sighs]

12:11.865 --> 12:14.232
So, it was 1925.

12:14.234 --> 12:18.169
You had just broken my heart,
so I came to st. Pierre,

12:18.304 --> 12:22.173
Where I'd heard that this
capone fella needed some guys

12:22.308 --> 12:25.243
To row rum out to the schooners

12:25.312 --> 12:27.779
Where the coast guard
couldn't find 'em.

12:27.781 --> 12:30.948
They were paying a fortune,
50 cents a gallon.

12:30.950 --> 12:32.584
I'd never seen money like that.

12:32.586 --> 12:34.852
I've never been good
with temptation.

12:34.888 --> 12:40.325
♪

12:40.460 --> 12:43.061
Well...

12:43.196 --> 12:46.464
Are you coming to hear
the rest of my confession?

12:50.003 --> 12:52.203
[chuckles]

12:53.373 --> 12:56.007
[laughter]

12:58.344 --> 13:01.078
<i> Où est votre professeur?</i>

13:01.114 --> 13:03.080
Uh...

13:03.116 --> 13:06.050
What's the french word
for "chaperone"?

13:12.259 --> 13:13.358
Voilà!

13:13.493 --> 13:14.692
Real french cheese.

13:14.828 --> 13:16.227
Ha-ha!

13:18.331 --> 13:20.164
You know, their cheese
doesn't come in slices.

13:20.200 --> 13:21.366
No?

13:21.501 --> 13:23.634
Uh, jars of whiz, then?

13:23.703 --> 13:25.236
They have all kinds.

13:25.371 --> 13:29.107
Camembert, brie,
and my favourite...

13:29.109 --> 13:31.376
Bleu!

13:31.511 --> 13:33.978
Ugh, that stuff reeks.

13:33.980 --> 13:35.412
You really had it before?

13:35.448 --> 13:37.448
Le fromage bleu?

13:37.517 --> 13:39.116
All the time!

13:39.152 --> 13:41.919
I have it with a cream cracker
with a cup of tea at bed time.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.654
Goes down smooth.

13:50.196 --> 13:51.329
Uh...

13:51.398 --> 13:54.399
I think it's a little off.

13:54.534 --> 13:56.600
It's supposed to be rotten,
dumbass.

13:56.636 --> 13:59.136
But you knew that, right?

13:59.138 --> 14:00.638
Yeah.

14:00.674 --> 14:02.607
I prefer mine more off.

14:02.742 --> 14:05.243
Mm-hm.

14:05.245 --> 14:06.543
Take another bite.

14:07.947 --> 14:09.213
Yeah?

14:09.216 --> 14:10.148
Yeah.

14:10.283 --> 14:11.482
Yeah!

14:14.487 --> 14:17.021
Yeah...
[retching]

14:29.035 --> 14:31.302
Oh, for the love of god, mike,

14:31.437 --> 14:33.371
I will shove
that radio up your arse

14:33.373 --> 14:35.439
And that'll be
the only action you get.

14:35.508 --> 14:37.375
Mike jr: [on radio]
and later on, we'll have

14:37.444 --> 14:39.243
Nightline with ron pumphrey,
but first...

14:39.246 --> 14:40.979
A request!

14:41.114 --> 14:43.514
Listening to our son is a bit of
a mood-killer, there, casanova!

14:43.516 --> 14:45.083
Mike jr: This is
mike critch jr.,

14:45.218 --> 14:48.186
And this one goes out to mom,
from dad...

14:48.321 --> 14:50.121
Which is kind of gross.

14:50.256 --> 14:54.125
Here's the fureys, with
"when you were sweet sixteen."

14:54.127 --> 14:56.027
Oh...

14:56.096 --> 14:58.796
<i> ♪ ...As I've never</i>
<i> loved before ♪</i>

14:58.798 --> 15:00.597
[mary chuckles softly]

15:02.435 --> 15:06.870
<i> ♪ since first I saw you</i>
<i> on the village... ♪</i>

15:06.907 --> 15:10.874
Oh, mike!

15:10.911 --> 15:13.144
I guess I'm just
out of practice.

15:13.146 --> 15:14.812
Can't blame me for being nervous

15:14.948 --> 15:16.280
Around the prettiest
girl that I've--

15:16.283 --> 15:18.015
Ah!

15:18.084 --> 15:20.151
Shut up and help me
move the beds together.

15:20.286 --> 15:25.756
<i> ♪ I love you as I loved you,</i>

15:25.792 --> 15:29.627
<i> When you were</i>
<i> sweet sixteen... ♪</i>

15:29.629 --> 15:32.630
Adult mark:<i> We were whatever</i>
<i>the french word for "lost" was.</i>

15:32.632 --> 15:35.566
Uh, I think it's this way.

15:35.702 --> 15:37.168
<i> Blaireau!</i>
<i> Arrête!</i>

15:37.237 --> 15:38.802
Adult mark:<i> French bullies!</i>

15:38.838 --> 15:41.406
<i> Like the fox brothers,</i>
<i> but with wine and smokes.</i>

15:41.541 --> 15:43.374
<i> Bonjour, mes amis.</i>

15:43.410 --> 15:46.477
<i> Du fromage... Bleu?</i>

15:46.612 --> 15:49.213
<i> Tu parles français</i>
<i> comme une vache espagnole!</i>

15:49.215 --> 15:52.150
<i> Ah, oui, oui.</i>
<i> Moi, aussi.</i>

15:52.152 --> 15:53.751
<i> T'es un vrai sans-couilles!</i>

15:53.820 --> 15:55.753
<i> Va te faire cuire un oeuf,</i>
<i> pompe à chiasse!</i>

15:55.888 --> 15:57.588
<i> Casse-toi donc, branleur!</i>

15:57.590 --> 15:59.624
Adult mark:<i> When it came</i>
<i> to french curse words,</i>

15:59.626 --> 16:03.361
<i> Fox wasn't a brain,</i>
<i> she was a genius!</i>

16:03.496 --> 16:07.264
<i> Ca m'est égal, espèce de</i>
<i> plouc!</i>

16:07.266 --> 16:09.400
I was just about to say
the same thing.

16:09.469 --> 16:10.934
Here.

16:13.606 --> 16:16.674
You must think I'm whatever
the french word for an idiot is.

16:16.809 --> 16:18.008
[french pronunciation]
idiot.

16:18.044 --> 16:20.011
No.

16:20.013 --> 16:21.979
You were actually pretty cute.

16:24.818 --> 16:29.620
So, can you just admit you can
read the street signs now?

16:29.622 --> 16:31.922
[sighs]
it's this way.

16:35.228 --> 16:37.762
Uh, what's a "branleur"?

16:37.831 --> 16:39.964
You're not old enough to know.

16:40.099 --> 16:42.967
-Sorry, come on.
-Oh...

16:46.339 --> 16:49.073
Ritche: Ah!
Yes, here it is!

16:49.208 --> 16:50.842
<i> "abandonné."</i>

16:50.844 --> 16:52.843
<i> Nous sommes...</i>

16:52.879 --> 16:55.379
<i> Abandonnés!</i>

16:55.515 --> 16:56.981
Brain!

17:00.320 --> 17:02.286
Ah, hurry up!

17:02.422 --> 17:05.856
Oh, god, this was so much
easier the first time around.

17:05.925 --> 17:09.026
Well, what's down there
that's so damn important?

17:09.029 --> 17:11.862
Pop: A few bottles in my load
kind of got...

17:11.931 --> 17:14.331
Went missing.

17:14.401 --> 17:17.868
Well, they came looking
for me, but you know,

17:17.937 --> 17:21.172
You really don't want to
be crossing al capone.

17:21.241 --> 17:24.775
♪

17:24.778 --> 17:28.479
♪

17:28.481 --> 17:30.514
Find him!

17:30.583 --> 17:32.617
Pop: I left something
in this church.

17:32.619 --> 17:36.086
I just wanted to see
whether it was still there.

17:36.122 --> 17:37.421
Aah!

17:37.424 --> 17:39.490
Yes!

17:39.625 --> 17:40.691
Oh!
[chuckles]

17:40.760 --> 17:43.160
They'd kill me
if they came back here!

17:43.296 --> 17:44.428
But thank god they're all dead.

17:44.464 --> 17:46.230
So screw 'em.

17:46.266 --> 17:48.499
Now...

17:48.634 --> 17:50.701
What do you know?

17:50.837 --> 17:53.971
[cackling excitedly]

17:53.973 --> 17:55.072
Someone will hear!

17:55.207 --> 17:56.440
[loud crash]
aah!

17:56.476 --> 17:57.975
Oh, jesus!

17:58.044 --> 17:59.376
No, no!

17:59.446 --> 18:01.512
Good god...

18:01.647 --> 18:02.647
Oh!

18:02.649 --> 18:04.381
Rats' piss!

18:04.383 --> 18:06.050
-They've eaten the money!
-[distant voices]

18:06.185 --> 18:08.920
My god, don't you people
ever clean these churches?

18:09.055 --> 18:09.954
Someone's coming!

18:09.956 --> 18:11.122
Alright, alright, alright.

18:11.257 --> 18:12.990
There was one more little thing.

18:13.126 --> 18:14.925
Leave it, you old fool!

18:14.994 --> 18:16.793
Oh-ho!

18:16.830 --> 18:18.329
Well!

18:18.331 --> 18:20.398
Welcome, my old beauty!

18:20.400 --> 18:21.599
Look at that!

18:21.668 --> 18:23.000
Voice: Où êtes vous?

18:23.002 --> 18:25.002
Aah!
Patrick, come on!

18:25.071 --> 18:27.071
Hey!
Ay, ay, ay...

18:27.140 --> 18:30.074
[both laughing]

18:36.749 --> 18:39.016
Why do you pretend
you're not smart?

18:39.152 --> 18:40.885
I mean, if I knew
french like that--

18:40.887 --> 18:42.753
Every year, I get a new teacher,

18:42.822 --> 18:45.489
And the first thing they say is,
"I taught your brothers."

18:45.492 --> 18:47.892
From then on,
I'm stupid or I'm trouble.

18:48.027 --> 18:50.561
If I do well,
they say I cheated, so...

18:50.630 --> 18:52.496
Why bother?

18:52.565 --> 18:54.031
That's not fair.

18:54.067 --> 18:56.834
You shouldn't hide who you are.

18:56.836 --> 18:58.435
Look who's talking.

18:58.471 --> 19:01.104
I'm being serious.

19:01.141 --> 19:03.574
You're not your brothers.
You're really special.

19:08.681 --> 19:11.515
[laughs nervously]
what's-- what's that over there?

19:14.687 --> 19:15.853
That's newfoundland!

19:15.988 --> 19:17.321
Cool!

19:17.323 --> 19:18.923
It's pretty.

19:18.925 --> 19:22.193
From a distance.

19:22.195 --> 19:25.129
It's beautiful.

19:25.198 --> 19:28.732
Thought you said
France was better.

19:28.768 --> 19:30.935
Sometimes you have to be
away from something for a while

19:31.004 --> 19:33.137
To realize
how special it really is.

19:33.206 --> 19:36.874
[soft, emotional music]

19:37.009 --> 19:40.011
♪

19:40.146 --> 19:43.614
Uh, France have the poodle,

19:43.749 --> 19:47.485
But we have the newfoundland dog
and the labrador retriever.

19:47.487 --> 19:50.754
We even have our own
time zone, and...

19:50.790 --> 19:54.825
Oh, uh, we should get going.

19:54.894 --> 19:57.962
♪

19:58.031 --> 20:02.032
♪

20:04.804 --> 20:06.837
♪

20:06.906 --> 20:09.240
Pop: That guide... My god.

20:09.375 --> 20:11.242
I didn't understand
a word she was saying!

20:11.244 --> 20:13.110
[gasps]

20:13.179 --> 20:14.778
You don't speak french, do you?

20:14.847 --> 20:18.382
[laughs]
[uncorks bottle]

20:18.418 --> 20:20.117
Woo-hoo-hoo!

20:20.186 --> 20:22.386
Oh, shh!

20:22.388 --> 20:24.922
Mmm.

20:25.057 --> 20:27.858
Mmm...

20:27.927 --> 20:29.927
-Mmm... Ooh!
-Oh my god!

20:31.564 --> 20:32.863
Oh my...

20:32.899 --> 20:35.198
Oh...
Ooh!

20:35.235 --> 20:36.333
Yeah?

20:36.402 --> 20:38.269
You know...

20:38.338 --> 20:41.539
There are a lot of things
that don't get better with age,

20:41.541 --> 20:44.742
But you, my dear, do.

20:44.877 --> 20:47.344
Adult mark:<i> Sometimes you</i>
<i> have to be away from something</i>

20:47.380 --> 20:49.480
<i> To realize</i>
<i> just how special it is.</i>

20:49.549 --> 20:51.949
<i> Because it's all too easy</i>
<i> to take the things we love</i>

20:51.951 --> 20:53.084
<i> For granted.</i>

20:53.219 --> 20:55.019
Mike jr: [on radio]
and now, the weather!

20:55.021 --> 20:56.954
Tomorrow until Tuesday,
we can expect light showers

20:57.023 --> 20:58.289
On the avalon, followed by--

20:58.291 --> 20:59.823
Change the station, will ya?

20:59.892 --> 21:01.292
Mike jr: [on radio]
...And drizzle.

21:01.427 --> 21:02.159
Headin' into the weekend--

21:02.295 --> 21:03.294
Woo!

21:03.363 --> 21:04.829
Sacred heart, my back!

21:04.964 --> 21:06.230
Aah!

21:06.299 --> 21:08.231
Adult mark:<i> If you can</i>
<i> find someone to love you</i>

21:08.268 --> 21:09.700
<i> For who you really are...</i>

21:09.702 --> 21:13.537
<i> Well, that's what the french</i>
<i> call "l'amour vrai."</i>

21:13.539 --> 21:15.773
<i> True love.</i>

21:15.775 --> 21:19.176
♪

